/* ************************ WiBit.Net Video Tutorial ************************ */
/* ************************************************************************** */
Title          : Beginner CrashCourse Guide To Java Programming
Num Videos     : 13
Lesson Length  : 1 hour 4 minutes 47 seconds
Resolution     : 800 x 600
Codec Download : http://www.techsmith.com/download/codecs.asp 
Date Recorded  : 9/10/2006
Narrator(s)    : Bryan Stouffer, Kevin Willett
OS:            : SuSE Linux 10.0
Software       : NetBeans
Description    : One of the WiBit.Net students was starting a Data Structures 
                 class that used Java. For some reason, Towson taught all the 
                 students C++ during their freshmen years and threw Java at 
                 them out of the blue! Luckily, Kevin and Bryan had a case 
                 of beer, some Papa Johns, and a few hours to kill. Together 
                 they created a 13 video series to give to their friends to 
                 get them started so that they didn?t fall behind. This 
                 series assumes that you have some previous experience with 
                 C or C++. Programming concepts are not explained fully, but 
                 it is a great tool to learn by example.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-= Video List -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
Video 1        : Installing Software
Video 2        : Math Tables
Video 3        : Code Explanation
Video 4        : Temperature Table 1
Video 5        : Temperature Table 2
Video 6        : Methods
Video 7        : Methods Recursion
Video 8        : Fibonacci
Video 9        : Fibonacci Input
Video 10       : SortFile 1: Input From File
Video 11       : SortFile 2: Populate Array
Videl 12       : SortFile 3: Sort Array
Video 13       : SortFile 3: Output To File
/* ************************************************************************** */
/* ***************************** About WiBit.Net **************************** */
/* ************************************************************************** */
WiBit was a website used by college students (and one professor) from Towson 
University in Baltimore, Maryland as a repository for learning materials. The
site creators were former Computer Science and Computer Security students, 
Kevin Willett and Bryan Stouffer. The first WiBit Tutorials were created by 
Kevin as a study aid for himself in late 2003. Over the following years Kevin
and Bryan decided to create a few tutorials and give themselves and their
fellow students a place to view and use them. Some were used as presentation
aids and students teaching students seminars. Over 30 tutorials were created!
The WiBit Tutorials served themselves well! All the students involved in the
project became professionals in their field of study. The creators Kevin and 
Bryan currently develop medical software. Others are working for great 
companies such as Bowing and Lockheed Martin. Since college the need to 
create tutorials has died down, but who knows what the future holds!
